&gt;Dave
&gt;--- yzzzguy@... wrote:
&gt;
&gt;From: &quot;Guy&quot; &lt;yzzzguy@...&gt;
&gt;To: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com
&gt;Subject: [EVP-ITC] Re: The Intelligence Project Description...
&gt;Date: Thu, 08 Mar 2007 03:51:25 -0000
&gt;
&gt;Hello, Suzette!
&gt;
&gt;The description was for a project that Scottish researcher Alexander
&gt;MacRae was funded for (by Bial - a pharmaceutical company in
&gt;Portugal). The questions given below were just an example of the
&gt;questions given on the charts attached to sound samples sent to
&gt;those of us on the international listening panel over these last 2
&gt;years. The project was just completed in December so you&#39;re no
&gt;longer able to be a part of it (sorry).
&gt;
&gt;As soon as I get permission from Alec - I&#39;ll post the final report
&gt;along with a chart and the samples for that particular chart (and a
&gt;few others I found interesting).
&gt;
&gt;Good luck in your own experiments!
&gt;
&gt;Guy
&gt;
&gt;--- In EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com, Suzette &lt;angel_ghost_spirit@...&gt;
&gt;wrote:
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; I would like to do the EVP experiment:
&gt; &gt;   I would like to start today....I will try at
&gt; &gt;   least 3 times to ask the following
&gt; &gt;   questions below. I will go into 3 different
&gt; &gt;   rooms of my house to record in each.
&gt; &gt;   When will we hear the results of the test?
&gt; &gt;   Will we be witten each personally on the results?
&gt; &gt;   Or how will we know how the spirits did.
&gt; &gt;   In the opinion of science that is!
&gt; &gt;   Angel
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; Guy &lt;yzzzguy@...&gt; wrote:
&gt; &gt;           [Note: the project is complete so don&#39;t try to sign up]
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; The Intelligence Project
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; A Project involving EVP and Listening
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; If you have done EVP for a while you will already know whether or
&gt; &gt; not what you say is responded to sometimes - you will already know
&gt; &gt; if there seems to be some sort of awareness there.
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; You may believe this to be so, and so may I, but the world in
&gt; &gt; general will just take this as further evidence of
&gt; &gt; our &quot;deteriorating mental ability&quot;!
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; You can&#39;t prove anything - all you can do is state your firm
&gt;belief
&gt; &gt; and perhaps back that up with some examples which you hope don&#39;t
&gt; &gt; sound too &quot;made-up&quot;.
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; This project aims to deal with that situation once and for all. We
&gt; &gt; believe in working with science rather than against it. Science is
&gt; &gt; not our enemy, nor indeed is scepticism.
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; Method
&gt; &gt; What we want to find out is if there is any relationship between
&gt; &gt; what the experimenter says and the type of EVP responses that we
&gt;get.
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; We are looking for signs of intelligence.
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; We want to do that in a measurable way - for that is the way of
&gt; &gt; science. And this is the way that has been approved by a major
&gt; &gt; European pharmaceutical company for funding.
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; We have six questions. These questions are decided on in advance.
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; During the experiment the experimenter asks each of the questions,
&gt; &gt; in turn, with a 30-second gap after each question to allow any
&gt; &gt; responses to be recorded.
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; So (for example) what you would get is,
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; Question &#39;What is the time?&#39;
&gt; &gt; [30 seconds delay];
&gt; &gt; Question &#39;What is your name?&#39;
&gt; &gt; [30 seconds delay],
&gt; &gt; Question &#39;What do you like best?&#39;
&gt; &gt; [30 second delay]
&gt; &gt; and so on.
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; Now if an utterance is heard within the 30-second period and if
&gt;the
&gt; &gt; utterance sounds as though it could be a response to the question,
&gt; &gt; then it is treated as an actual response. For example if we hear
&gt; &gt; the utterance &#39;John Smith&#39; seven seconds after the question &#39;What
&gt;is
&gt; &gt; your name?&#39; is asked, then that looks like a response to that
&gt; &gt; question.
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; The experimenter carries out the session, asking each of the
&gt; &gt; questions in turn; and then the recording of the session is turned
&gt; &gt; over to a speech analyst.
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; The analyst picks out from the general background noise all the
&gt; &gt; utterances he can find in the recording. He refines his search
&gt; &gt; still further by selecting out the 16 utterances of the best
&gt; &gt; quality. (sometimes it will be less than 16), and &quot;shuffles&quot; these
&gt; &gt; so that you will not know which came first, which came second and
&gt;so
&gt; &gt; on.
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; The final 16 utterances, their order shuffled, are sent out to you.
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; What you are asked to do is decide if any of the utterances could
&gt;be
&gt; &gt; a response to any of the questions, and to fill in a table like
&gt;that
&gt; &gt; shown in the example below.
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; Track No. Could be a response to Question Number��..
&gt; &gt; BR01 4
&gt; &gt; BR02 0
&gt; &gt; BR03 0
&gt; &gt; BRO4 3
&gt; &gt; BR05 1
&gt; &gt; BR06 2
&gt; &gt; BR07 3
&gt; &gt; BRO8 3
&gt; &gt; BR09 6
&gt; &gt; BR10 0
&gt; &gt; BR11 0
&gt; &gt; BR12 0
&gt; &gt; BR13 6
&gt; &gt; BR14 5
&gt; &gt; BR15 0
&gt; &gt; BR16 0
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; As you can see some utterances are not considered to be a response
&gt; &gt; to any of the questions, and so a &#39;0&#39; is inserted at that point.
&gt; &gt; This is not an easy test, that is why you are being asked to help.
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; Please send your results to XXX@... and then they will get put
&gt; &gt; into our database - and in time we will be told the results.
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; Meanwhile, however, preliminary results look quite promising and
&gt; &gt; your assistance on this vital project is very much appreciated!
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt;
&gt;~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; Guy
